ustrations to examine the challenges and opportunities facing the women as they toured both within the UK and further afield in North America and Australasia. It will appeal to students and researchers in theatre and performance history, Victorian studies, gender studies and transatlantic studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aActresseszGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aTheater and societyxHistoryy19th century. 0aTheater and societyzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aWomen in the theaterzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Theater / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aActress.  acareer.  agender.  ahistory.  anineteenth century.  aprofession.  atheatre.  atouring.  avictorian.1 aNorwood, Janice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613333540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526133335423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526133335/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles